<a name="newsitem975351890,75435,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Monday, Monday</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, November 27, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
As Velious draws closer the excitement begins to build. It also becomes apparent that we need to explain the way that our submission process works before the madness of expansion hits us. <br><br>First and foremost if you submit something and your email is returned with an error then please ignore it. Our staff is on a mailing list. Each mail is sent out to every member of the staff. On heavy submission days some staff members may be away and not able to check their mails. Their quota may become exceeded which will result in an error being returned to you. Please do not resend the submission. Every other member of the list has already received it. What happens here is that on days where traffic is already in large amounts it becomes compounded by half of our submissions being resent over and over again.<br><br>Secondly if you submit an item or quest and it is not posted immediately don't despair. I personally have three differnet systems which I update from. Some times I will download my email to one system then I won't be back to that location for a few days. As a result it is not uncommon for submissions to go a few days before posting. Items which are already cropped and ready to go are usually posted first during times of heavy submissions as they are the easiest to get to. If a week or more goes by and your submission is still not posted then it may have been lost in the shuffle and feel free to re-submit.<br><br>Enough of that, to the update!<br><br>New 1HSlashs: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/katanaofendurance.html">Katana of Endurance</a>.<br>New 1HBlunts: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/guardiansmace.html">Guardian's Mace</a>.<br>New 2HBlunts: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/gorgonheadstaff.html">Gorgon Head Staff</a>(NEC), <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/bluecyrstalstaff.html">Blue Crystal Staff</a>(WIZ).<br>New Leggings: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/dreadscalegreaves.html">Dreadscale Greaves</a>(SHD), <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/scaledmysticgreaves.html">Scaled Mystic Greaves</a>(SHM).<br>New Boots: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/scaledmysticboots.html">Scaled Mystic Boots</a>(SHM).<br>New Bracers: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/scaledmysticbracers.html">Scaled Mystic Bracers</a>(SHM).<br>New Cloaks: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/scaledmysticcloak.html">Scaled Mystic Cloak</a>(SHM).<br>New Quests: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/scaledmysticarmor.html">Scaled Mystic Armor</a>(SHM).<br>Updated Quests: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/poanecromancer.html">Plane of Air Necromancer Quests</a>.<br>Updated Veeshan's Peak Spawns: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/ultra/hoshkar.html">Hoshkar</a>.<br>Updated Kedge Keep Spawns: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/notsocommon/kedgekeep/phinigelautropos.html">Phinigel Autropos</a>.<br>Updated Howling Stones Spawns: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/notsocommon/charisis/skeletalsepulcher.html">Skeletal Sepulcher</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem975295410,89595,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Permanent Death in the MMRPG</font> </strong><small>Posted Sunday, November 26, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
While not exactly Everquest related I figured that some viewers might be interested in knowing that I have posted up a new article at GameZNet. This article takes a look at <a href="http://gameznet.com/tech/mmrpg3/">Permanent Death in the MMRPG</a>. It covers the benefits of permanent death and how it could work. I know this is a controversial subject but the goal here isn't to convince people that a permanent death system is the way to go. The goal is simply to get players and developers to consider it. <br><br>Since posting this article it has been brought to my attention that there is an MMRPG in development which promises permanent death. For more information click <a href="http://www.glitchless.com/">here</a>.<br><br>New Article: <a href="http://gameznet.com/tech/mmrpg3/">Permanent Death in the MMRPG</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem975096823,93022,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">SK Epic Quest Completed</font> </strong><small>Posted Friday, November 24, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
The shadowknight epic quest was completed last night by Xate. I wanted to offer up a congradulations to him as well as to the many others who contributed to the quest along the way such as Manr, Ningauble and Arioc. This leaves magicians as the only class who have yet to complete their epic quest. <br><br>Below is the SK epic quest weapon, the final piece of elder spiritist armor(which had not been in game until now for reasons that remain to be seen) and the complete spoiler for the shadowknight quest.<br><br>New 2HSlashs: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/innoruukscurse.html">Innoruuk's Curse</a>(SHD).<br>New Boots: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/elderspiritistsboots.html">Elder Spiritist's Boots</a>(DRU).<br>New Effects: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/effects/soulconsumption.html">Soul Consumption</a>.<br>Updated Magic Armor Sets: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/elderarmor.html">Elder Spiritist's Armor</a>(DRU).<br>Updated Quests: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/skepicquest.html">Shadowknight Epic Quest</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/heartofaninnocent.html">Heart of an Innocent</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/willofinnoruuk.html">The Will of Innoruuk</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest/headofthevaliant.html">Head of the Valiant</a>.
